This animal lover was enjoying the trip of a lifetime when she was brought back down to earth with a bump by a grumpy elephant . 
American student Whitney Lavaux wanted to get closer to nature - and certainly managed that after stumbling upon elephants being washed by locals in Chiang Mai. 
She decided to lend a helping hand and began brushing the mighty beast's trunk as a pal filmed. 
But the majestic creature was evidently camera-shy - and suddenly lobbed Whitney into the air with a thrust of its tusks. 
The friend can be heard gasping as she rushes to help Whitney, who lands on the backside in ankle-deep muddy water. 
Thankfully the student was unhurt. Read More 
And apparently the incident inspired a new sport. 
She gave the video the tongue-in-cheek caption "Elephlying in Thailand" when she uploaded it on YouTube . Like us on Facebook
